dreams.dream: My mam suggested me and my partner take a trip to Wales where his father's family comes from she flys over with us. When we arrive I ask my partner to point out on a map where his dad grew up we follow that and arrive at a peir looking into the ocean we jump onto a big rock where I get a old skeleton key after we jump back to shore my mam tells me the key is very important and to keep it safe and she said it was very important my brother gets one too. Then I say to my partner this isn't your family home and then our 3yr old son appears and I ask him to lead the way he does we come upon a old town house for sale and the owner doesn't know about his family so we continue on then we see an old row of cottages I point to one and tell my partner his dad's mam used to live there. Then an old yorkie dog comes up and my son chases after him and we land in a n old lady's sitting room who is asleep on the sofa the dog stops and lies down beside my exs brothers birthcert who was born shortly before his dad died we woke the lady up to ask her about it but she tells us we are not supposed to be here. My ex spots his dad out the window and knocks on it when his dad comes in he gets mad at him and asks him where he's been all these years he said he never left and was always right here. He then asks how we found him I point at my son and said he led us here this is your grandson he then picks him up under his arm and swoops him around in an aeroplane motion. We all go to sit on the couch and I wake up
dreams.interpretation:
This dream appears to be a combination of various symbols and themes that could hold personal significance to you. However, I can provide a general analysis based on the elements present in your dream.

The dream seems to revolve around the exploration of your partner's family roots and the discovery of hidden information or connections. The trip to Wales represents a quest for knowledge about your partner's father's family. Your mother's presence suggests her support and guidance in this journey.

The key symbolizes access to important information or insights. It may represent an opportunity to unlock secrets or uncover hidden truths about your partner's family history. The fact that both you and your brother receive keys suggests that this journey is significant for your entire family.

Upon arriving at the pier, the ocean represents the vastness of the unknown. Jumping onto the rock could symbolize taking a courageous leap into the exploration of your partner's family past. Finding the old skeleton key on the rock suggests that this journey will lead to the discovery of something valuable and potentially life-changing.

When your three-year-old son appears, he becomes the guide for your exploration. His presence may symbolize innocence, intuition, or a connection to a higher power. Following him leads you to an old townhouse and later to the row of cottages, which signifies getting closer to discovering your partner's family roots.

Encountering the old lady's sitting room and finding your ex's brother's birth certificate among her belongings suggests stumbling upon significant documents or records. The presence of the old Yorkshire dog may symbolize loyalty, protection, or a connection to the past.

Finally, meeting your partner's father, who was previously believed to have been absent, suggests a surprise reunion or the resolution of unanswered questions. His initial anger may reflect unresolved issues or emotions tied to his absence. However, his act of picking up your son and celebrating his presence suggests a joyful reunion and the restoration of family bonds.

Overall, this dream appears to convey a journey of discovery, connection, and resolution within your partner's family. It may also highlight the significance of intuition and the guidance of your child in finding important truths or reunions.
dreams.title: Journey to the Forgotten Heritage: Uncovering Family Secrets in Wales

dreams.dream: Was in a huge cruise where they would go around the world and back to where we started. It was very fancy and I felt out of place. When asking someone for help, they avoided eye contacted and looked at me with disgust. The person seemed very rich and she seemed to not like me around. I wanted to leave but couldn't because it was in the middle of the trip.
dreams.interpretation: This dream may represent feelings of being out of place or uncomfortable in a new or unfamiliar environment. The cruise ship could represent a journey or adventure that you are on in your waking life. The feeling of being looked down upon or avoided by someone on the trip may indicate feelings of insecurity or inferiority. It could be helpful to evaluate whether these feelings are based on reality or if they stem from your own self-doubt. Additionally, feeling trapped or unable to leave could point to a sense of being stuck in a situation in your waking life. Consider examining any current situations or relationships that may be making you feel this way and focus on making positive changes to improve your confidence and self-worth.
dreams.title: Lost in Luxury: A Disconcerting Journey on the Lavish World Cruise

dreams.dream: I dreamed about running away from someone or something that is always in the sky or feels like it's everywhere watching me. This something or someone want to hurt me really bad and wants me to suffer for as long as they can, even going to the extent of not letting me die to make me suffer more.
dreams.interpretation: Running away from something or someone that wants to hurt you in a dream can represent feelings of stress, anxiety or fear in your waking life. The fact that this thing is always in the sky or feels like it's everywhere watching you might indicate that you feel like you’re being constantly watched or judged by someone or something. The desire to hurt you and make you suffer could represent your own negative self-talk or self-sabotaging behavior, or it could be a manifestation of external pressures that are causing you pain. The dream may be a reflection of your subconscious desire to escape from these pressures and find a way to protect yourself from harm. Consider identifying any sources of stress and anxiety in your waking life and seeking ways to mitigate or eliminate them.
dreams.title: Surrounded by Skies of Despair: A Relentless Pursuit of Pain
